Turkey Financial Industry Profit Falls $1 Billion in First Half

-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 
2011-08-27T10:30:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-27/turkey-financial-industry-profit-falls-1-billion-in-first-half.html
Turkish financial industry profit
fell 1.8 billion liras ($1.03 billion) in the first six months
of the year from the same period in 2010, hurt by lower  interest
rates , according to a  report  from the banking regulator.  Total financial industry profit over the period was 10.3
billion liras, according to the report by the Ankara-based
Banking Regulation and Supervision Agency. The value of
financial industry assets rose to 1.48 trillion liras, the
agency said.  Non-performing loans declined to 2.9 percent of total
loans, according to the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Benjamin Harvey in Istanbul at 
 bharvey11@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
